HEADWORD: Mozzetta
<hw>Moz*zet"ta</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>mozzetta</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>mosette</ets>. Cf. <er>Amice</er> a hood or cape.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A cape, with a small hood; -- worn by the pope
and other dignitaries of the Roman Catholic Church.</def>⟦br⟧
